The Chronicle Sikhumbuzo Moyo, Online Reporter ALERT members of the public in Beitbridge yesterday apprehended two alleged armed robbers who had lured an illegal money changer to a secluded place. <img class="size-large wp-image-682010" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/02/unnamed-1-3-680x380.png" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/02/unnamed-1-3.png 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/02/unnamed-1-3-360x200.png 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The mob that beat the suspected robbers. Picture credit: Ministry of Information, Publicity and Broadcasting Services Initially, there were three suspects, but one escaped. The crowd beat the duo until they fell unconscious. <img class="size-large wp-image-682012" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/02/unnamed-2-2-680x380.png" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/02/unnamed-2-2.png 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/02/unnamed-2-2-360x200.png 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> A firearm that was retrieved from the duo. Picture credit: Ministry of Information, Publicity and Broadcasting Services According to the Permanent Secretary in the Ministry of Information, Publicity and Broadcasting Services Mr Nick Mangwana, the trio also tried to hijack the victim’s car. <img class="size-large wp-image-682014" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/02/unnamed-3-1-680x380.png" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/02/unnamed-3-1.png 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/02/unnamed-3-1-360x200.png 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> A firearm that was retrieved from the duo. Picture credit: Ministry of Information, Publicity and Broadcasting Services “Yesterday three alleged armed robbers lured an illicit currency dealer to a secluded place through a phone call pretending to be genuine clients. They tried to hijack his car and he fought them, had tyre burst. One escaped and two were apprehended by members of the public,” wrote Mr Mangwana on his Twitter timeline. @skhumoyo2000